There are several ways to center a div in CSS, depending on what type of centering you need. Here are the most common methods:

## 1. Horizontal Centering

### Using `margin: auto`
```css
.center-horizontal {
  width: 300px; /* Must have a defined width */
  margin: 0 auto;
}
```

### Using Flexbox
```css
.parent {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: center;
}
```

## 2. Vertical Centering

### Using Flexbox
```css
.parent {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  height: 100vh; /* or any specific height */
}
```

## 3. Both Horizontal and Vertical Centering

### Method 1: Flexbox (Recommended)
```css
.parent {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: center;
  align-items: center;
  height: 100vh;
}
```

### Method 2: CSS Grid
```css
.parent {
  display: grid;
  place-items: center;
  height: 100vh;
}
```

### Method 3: Absolute Positioning with Transform
```css
.parent {
  position: relative;
  height: 100vh;
}

.center {
  position: absolute;
  top: 50%;
  left: 50%;
  transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
}
```

